page.title: 04Winster valley vegetaion
page.content: None of the roads in the valley has been treated with weedkiller for some years, so the vegetation is abundant. On and over the walls in the higher land are brambles and raspberries and where the verges are near water there are crops of many varieties of rushes, grasses and bog plants. Heather, foxgloves, broom, gorse, bracken, thistles, small trees which are self-sown, such as silver birch and ash. Clover and rough grazing for cattle and sheep, rabbits and roe deer. No large plantations, much self-sown. Larch trees at Knipe Tarn are very lovely.
